---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { SITE } from '../config';
import { rotateCTA } from '../utils/cta';
const cta = rotateCTA('sell-house-cash-today');

const faqSchema = {
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "FAQPage",
  "mainEntity": [
    { "@type": "Question", "name": "Can you actually buy my house today?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "We can quote your house today and have a written offer to you today or tomorrow morning. The legal closing — funds in your account — takes 7-21 days typical because title work, lender payoff, and HOA estoppels all take time. The 'today' part is the quote + decision; the close is days away." } },
    { "@type": "Question", "name": "What's the absolute fastest you've closed?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Seven business days, on a clean-title owner-occupied house with no liens and no HOA. Add 3-7 days if there's a mortgage payoff; add another 5-10 if there's HOA. Probate, short sales, or estate properties take 30+ days." } },
    { "@type": "Question", "name": "Do you give a quote over the phone?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "We give a quote range over the phone based on what you tell us about the property. We confirm with a specific number after a quick walk-through, typically within 24-72 hours of the initial call." } },
  ],
};
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Sell My House for Cash Today in Arizona | Cash Guy Nate"
  description="Same-day cash quote on your AZ house. Written offer within 24 hours. Close in 7-21 days. No fees, no repairs. Call (602) 555-0100 now."
  schema={faqSchema}
  pageType="service"
  crumbs={[{ label: "Home", href: "/" }, { label: "Sell House Cash Today" }]}
>
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="container">
      <span class="hero__kicker">Same-Day Quote · 7-21 Day Close</span>
      <h1>Sell Your House for Cash Today in Arizona</h1>
      <p class="hero__sub">Call us this morning, get a quote this afternoon, have a written offer by tomorrow. Closing happens in 7-21 days from there. No fees, no repairs, no buyer financing risk.</p>
      <a href={`tel:${SITE.phone}`} class="btn btn--large">{cta}</a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="container container--narrow">
    <h2>What "sell today" actually means</h2>
    <p>
      You can't legally close a real estate transaction in a single day in Arizona — title work, lender payoffs, and HOA estoppels all require time. But you can lock in a written offer the same day you call, which is what most sellers searching "sell my house cash today" are actually looking for: certainty that there's a buyer, certainty on price, certainty on timeline.
    </p>
    <p>
      We deliver that. Call (602) 555-0100. Within the call, we'll quote a range based on your property. Within 24-72 hours, we walk the property and confirm a specific written offer. From signed contract to wired funds in your account: 7-21 days typical.
    </p>
    <p>
      The full process: <a href="/how-it-works/">how it works</a>.
    </p>

    <h2>When same-day quotes make sense</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>You have a hard deadline (pre-foreclosure trustee sale, military PCS, court date)</li>
      <li>You've decided to sell and want the process started immediately</li>
      <li>You're comparing offers and need quick numbers from multiple buyers</li>
      <li>Property has been on the market and you're switching strategies</li>
      <li>Out-of-state situation where you need to plan around limited travel</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>What you need to share on the call</h2>
    <p>Five quick pieces of information are enough for an initial quote:</p>
    <ol>
      <li>Property address</li>
      <li>Approximate year of construction</li>
      <li>Rough condition (move-in / dated / deferred / distressed)</li>
      <li>What's going on (relocation, estate, divorce, etc.)</li>
      <li>Your ideal close timeline</li>
    </ol>

    <h2>Same-day timeline example</h2>
    <p>Here's what a typical "I called this morning" day looks like:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>9:14 AM</strong> — You call (602) 555-0100. We answer. Five-minute conversation about the property, your situation, your timeline.</li>
      <li><strong>9:22 AM</strong> — We've pulled comps in real-time during the call. Quote range delivered: e.g., "$285K to $312K based on what you've told me."</li>
      <li><strong>9:30 AM</strong> — If you want to move forward, we schedule the walk-through. We aim for same-day if possible, next morning otherwise.</li>
      <li><strong>2:45 PM (same day)</strong> — Walk-through complete. We confirm condition, refine our number to a specific figure.</li>
      <li><strong>5:00 PM</strong> — Written purchase agreement delivered to your inbox.</li>
      <li><strong>Next day</strong> — You review (or your attorney reviews) overnight, sign or counter the next morning.</li>
      <li><strong>Day 3-5</strong> — Escrow opens, title company orders payoff demands and HOA estoppels.</li>
      <li><strong>Day 10-18</strong> — Title clears, you sign closing docs, funds wire to your account.</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      That's the full sequence from "I'm thinking about it this morning" to "money in my account" in 10-18 days. The "today" piece — the quote + decision — happens in hours. The legal close is days away because Arizona title work, lender coordination, and HOA paperwork all have inherent timelines we can't compress past a certain point.
    </p>

    <h2>What makes a same-day quote actually accurate</h2>
    <p>
      Some cash buyers will quote anything just to lock you up; their "same-day offer" is followed by post-inspection price drops of 8-20%. That's not what we do. Our day-one quote range becomes a specific number after a walk-through, and that number then holds through closing 90%+ of the time.
    </p>
    <p>
      The way we keep our quote accurate from day one: we operate in Arizona only, primarily in the Phoenix metro + Tucson + the I-10 corridor. We've underwritten hundreds of houses in these markets. When you describe a 1985 ranch in central Mesa, we know what the comps are doing because we just closed two of them last quarter. The "quote range" we give on the phone reflects real underwriting, not a number designed to lock you up.
    </p>

    <h2>Common questions</h2>
    <div class="faq">
      <div class="faq__item"><p class="faq__q">Can you actually buy my house today?</p><p class="faq__a">We can quote today and have a written offer to you today or tomorrow morning. The legal closing takes 7-21 days because title work, lender payoff, and HOA estoppels need time. The "today" part is the quote + decision.</p></div>
      <div class="faq__item"><p class="faq__q">What's the absolute fastest you've closed?</p><p class="faq__a">Seven business days, on a clean-title owner-occupied house with no liens and no HOA.</p></div>
      <div class="faq__item"><p class="faq__q">Do you give a quote over the phone?</p><p class="faq__a">Yes — a range based on what you tell us. The specific number comes after a quick walk-through within 24-72 hours.</p></div>
      <div class="faq__item"><p class="faq__q">What if the quote you give me today doesn't hold?</p><p class="faq__a">Our day-one quote holds 90%+ of the time through closing. We only adjust if the walk-through reveals something material we couldn't see without being on-site. Routine condition variations are factored into our initial range.</p></div>
    </div>

    <div class="inline-disclaimer">
      <strong>Cash buyer disclosure:</strong> {SITE.brandName} buys as a principal investor — not a broker. Offers are typically below open-market value in exchange for speed and certainty.
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="cta-section">
    <div class="container container--narrow">
      <h2>Call now for today's quote</h2>
      <p>Five minutes on the phone. Same-day quote range. Tomorrow's written offer. Close in 7-21 days.</p>
      <a href={`tel:${SITE.phone}`} class="btn btn--large">Call {SITE.phoneDisplay}</a>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
